Phono-semantic compound ( 形聲 / 形声 ): semantic 屮 ( “ sprout ” ) + phonetic 六 ( OC *ruɡ ) .
If interpreted as the upper part of 夌 ( líng ), this character 𡴆 / 圥 is its proto-form as an ideogrammic compound ( 會意 / 会意 ): 木 ( “ tree ” ) + 人 ( “ person ” ) meaning "to climb; to surpass." When the original character was modified into 夌 , the character 𡴆 / 圥 fell into disuse.
